# Hidden Work Engine™ — The Iceberg (Spec 118)

**Full document:** `docs/SPARK_HIDDEN_WORK_ENGINE_FRAMEWORK.md`

**Philosophy:** [Spec 111 Iceberg](../docs/SPARK_HOSPITALITY_FRAMEWORK.md) · **Triggers:** [Spec 114 Flow Engine](../docs/SPARK_CONVERSATION_FLOW_ENGINE_FRAMEWORK.md) · **Brain work:** [Spec 117](../docs/SPARK_BUSINESS_BRAIN_MEMORY_RETRIEVAL_FRAMEWORK.md) · **QA:** [Spec 116 Gold Standards](../docs/SPARK_CONVERSATION_GOLD_STANDARDS_FRAMEWORK.md)

## Iceberg

~10% visible: Shari's response, one next step.

~90% submerged: organize assets · research · connect projects · draft · remember · scan gaps.

**Member never feels busy. Spark does.**

## Core rules

1. **Response ships first** — hidden work never blocks conversation
2. **Default invisible** — no spinners, progress bars, "I'm organizing…"
3. **Permission before surface** — drafts, wins, new assets (Spec 106 Rule 5)
4. **Cancel silently** when member changes direction — no sunk-cost guilt
5. **Fail silent** — retry internally; never alarm member

## Work categories

Memory: `brain_retrieve` · `brain_propose_write` · `brain_connect` · `win_capture`

Assets: `asset_organize` · `project_connect` · `autosave` · `asset_create_prep`

Creation: `research_prep` · `draft_prep` · `content_prep`

Intelligence: `gap_analysis` · `opportunity_scan` · `pattern_observe` · `anticipate_next`

## When wrong — diff gold standards

Missing work? Surfaced too early? Blocked response? Violated permission?

Compare `docs/conversation-gold-standards/` **Hidden work** section per turn.

**Types:** `lib/sparkHiddenWorkEngine/types.ts`

**Spec 106 wins on conflict.**
